Cell.Text: [S] Easy, easy. Don't get up so quickly. | How are you feeling?

Cell.Text: No, I saved your life. My arrow was tipped with a unique paralytic poison. It slowed your heart and kept you from bleeding out. | Had I intended to kill you, we wouldn't be having this conversation.

Node.Caption: TG05KarliahIntroBranchTopic01: Hold on... you shot me!

Cell.Text: My original intention was to use that arrow on Mercer, but I never had a clear shot. | I made a split second decision to get you out of the way and it prevented your death.
More than you'll ever realize. The posion on that arrow took me a year to perfect; I only had enough for a single shot.

Without the antidote I administered, you'd be as still as a statue. I treated your wounds and didn't leave you defenseless. | The poison on that arrow took me a year to perfect; I only had enough for a single shot and yet I used it on you.
I promise you, the thought crossed my mind. The posion on that arrow took me a year to perfect; I only had enough for a single shot.

Node.Caption: TG05KarliahIntroBranchTopic01az: You should have shot Mercer instead.

Cell.Text: Mercer must be brought before the Guild to answer for what he's done. He needs to pay for Gallus's murder.
[S] All I had hoped was to capture Mercer alive.

My purpose in using Snow Veil Sanctum to ambush Mercer wasn't simply for irony's sake. | Before both of you arrived, I recovered a journal from Gallus's remains. I suspect the information we need is written inside.

Node.Caption: TG05KarliahIntroConBranch01: How will you prove it now?

Cell.Text: [S] I wish I knew. The journal is written in some sort of language I've never seen before.
Enthir... Gallus's friend at the College of Winterhold. Of course... | It's the only outsider Gallus trusted with the knowledge of his Nightingale identity.

[S] There were three of us. Myself, Gallus and Mercer. We were a anonymous splinter of the Thieves Guild in Riften. | Perhaps I'll tell you more about it later. Right now, you need to head for Winterhold with the journal and get the translation.
